<paragraph id="8BFD45513613D07B56E4FEE6FB754A78" blockId="25.[151,1102,281,305]" box="[151,1102,281,305]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
For more complete lists of synonymies see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD338A03613D07B543CFEE6FDD24A78" author="Boucek, Z." box="[591,745,281,305]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" refId="ref18491" refString="Boucek, Z. (1988) Australasian Chalcidoidea (Hymenoptera): A Biosystematic Revision of Genera of Fourteen Families, with a Reclassification of Species. CAB International, Wallingford, 832 pp." type="book" year="1988">Bouček (1988)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD338A03613D07B5480FEE6FCB74A78" author="Schauff, M. E." box="[755,908,281,305]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="1 - 109" refId="ref20147" refString="Schauff, M. E. (1991) The Holarctic genera of Entedoninae (Hymenoptera: Eulophidae). Contributions of the American Entomological Institute, 26 (4), 1 - 109." type="journal article" year="1991">Schauff (1991)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD338A03613D07B55CFFEE6FB714A78" author="Noyes, J. S." box="[956,1098,281,305]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" refId="ref20012" refString="Noyes, J. S. (2019) Universal Chalcidoidea Database. World Wide Web electronic publication. Available from: http: // www. nhm. ac. uk / chalcidoids (accessed 9 April 2021)" type="url" year="2019">Noyes (2019)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFD45513613D07B56E4FEA0FA704967" blockId="25.[151,1436,351,558]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<taxonomicName id="4C423ED23613D07B56E4FEA0FE6B4A30" box="[151,336,351,377]" class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" genus="Chrysonotomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93699433613D07B56E4FEA0FE6B4A30" box="[151,336,351,377]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Chrysonotomyia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a cosmopolitan genus currently with 172 described species (
<bibRefCitation id="EFD338A03613D07B5251FEA0FB8B4A30" author="Noyes, J. S." box="[1058,1200,351,377]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" refId="ref20012" refString="Noyes, J. S. (2019) Universal Chalcidoidea Database. World Wide Web electronic publication. Available from: http: // www. nhm. ac. uk / chalcidoids (accessed 9 April 2021)" type="url" year="2019">Noyes 2019</bibRefCitation>
). It is predominantly Neotropical (107 species described); 12 species are known from 
<collectingCountry id="F35505C13613D07B5506FE7CFC944AD4" box="[885,943,387,413]" name="India" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">India</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFD338A03613D07B55CCFE7CFB764AD4" author="Noyes, J. S." box="[959,1101,387,413]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" refId="ref20012" refString="Noyes, J. S. (2019) Universal Chalcidoidea Database. World Wide Web electronic publication. Available from: http: // www. nhm. ac. uk / chalcidoids (accessed 9 April 2021)" type="url" year="2019">Noyes 2019</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="4C423ED23613D07B5213FE7CFA224AD4" authority="Ashmead" authorityName="Ashmead" box="[1120,1305,387,413]" class="Insecta" family="Eulophidae" genus="Chrysonotomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93699433613D07B5213FE7CFA224AD4" box="[1120,1305,387,413]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Chrysonotomyia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species are reported as primary egg and larval parasitoids of leaf-mining 
<taxonomicName id="4C423ED23613D07B5521FE58FC9D4A88" box="[850,934,423,449]" class="Insecta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Diptera</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C423ED23613D07B55C5FE58FB684A88" box="[950,1107,423,449]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Agromyzidae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C423ED23613D07B522CFE58FA364A8B" box="[1119,1293,423,450]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Cecidomyiidae</taxonomicName>
), 
<taxonomicName id="4C423ED23613D07B5352FE58FAA74A88" box="[1313,1436,423,449]" class="Insecta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Coleoptera</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C423ED23613D07B56ECFE34FE1C4AAC" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1815" box="[159,295,459,485]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Buprestidae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C423ED23613D07B5716FE34FD2B4AAF" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[357,528,459,486]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Chrysomelidae</taxonomicName>
) and some hemipterous insects (
<bibRefCitation id="EFD338A03613D07B55E2FE34FB154AAC" author="Schauff, M. E." box="[913,1070,459,485]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="1 - 109" refId="ref20147" refString="Schauff, M. E. (1991) The Holarctic genera of Entedoninae (Hymenoptera: Eulophidae). Contributions of the American Entomological Institute, 26 (4), 1 - 109." type="journal article" year="1991">Schauff 1991</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD338A03613D07B524DFE33FBF54AAC" author="Noyes, J. S." box="[1086,1230,459,486]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" refId="ref20012" refString="Noyes, J. S. (2019) Universal Chalcidoidea Database. World Wide Web electronic publication. Available from: http: // www. nhm. ac. uk / chalcidoids (accessed 9 April 2021)" type="url" year="2019">Noyes 2019</bibRefCitation>
). Some important taxonomic works on the genus are by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD338A03613D07B544AFE10FDEC4940" author="Askew, R. R." box="[569,727,495,521]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="27 - 31" refId="ref18304" refString="Askew, R. R. (1979) Taxonomy of some European Chrysonotomyia Ashmead (Hymenoptera: Eulophidae) with description of C. ongiventris n. sp. and notes on distribution. Entomologica Scandinavica, 10 (1), 27 - 31. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 187631279 X 00376" type="journal article" year="1979">Askew (1979)</bibRefCitation>
(NW European species), 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD338A03613D07B5580FE10FBA24940" author="Boucek, Z." box="[1011,1177,495,521]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" refId="ref18491" refString="Boucek, Z. (1988) Australasian Chalcidoidea (Hymenoptera): A Biosystematic Revision of Genera of Fourteen Families, with a Reclassification of Species. CAB International, Wallingford, 832 pp." type="book" year="1988">Bouček (1988)</bibRefCitation>
(Australasian species), 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD338A03613D07B56E4FDEBFE0C4964" author="Hansson, C." box="[151,311,531,558]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="29 - 52" refId="ref19090" refString="Hansson, C. (1990) A taxonomic study on the Palearctic species of Chrysonotomyia Ashmead and Neochrysocharis Kurdjumov (Hymenoptera: Eulophidae), Entomology Scandinavian, 21 (1), 29 - 52. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 187631290 X 00021" type="journal article" year="1990">Hansson 1990</bibRefCitation>
(Palearctic species), 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD338A03613D07B5456FDEBFDFF4964" author="Hansson, C." box="[549,708,531,558]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="1 - 536" refId="ref19140" refString="Hansson, C. (2004) Eulophidae of Costa Rica. 2. Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute, 75, 1 - 536." type="journal article" year="2004">Hansson 2004</bibRefCitation>
(Neotropical species) and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD338A03613D07B5583FDECFBB04964" author="Jamali, M. M." box="[1008,1163,531,557]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" refId="ref19234" refString="Jamali, M. M. (2018) AReviewofIndiangeneraofthesubfamilyEntedoninae (Hymenoptera: Chalcidoidea: Eulophidae). (Doctoral thesis). Department of Zoology, Aligarh Muslim University, Aligarh (UP), India." type="book" year="2018">Jamali (2018)</bibRefCitation>
(Indian species).
</paragraph>
